00:06:06.440 --> 00:06:08.960
JEFFREY GROSSMAN:
Bloch's theorem.

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:12.620
And we don't need to know
much about Bloch's theorem

00:06:12.620 --> 00:06:16.130
except the endgame.

00:06:16.130 --> 00:06:18.020
The key is what it means.

00:06:18.020 --> 00:06:24.050
And it's a mathematical
consequence.

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:30.620
It's a consequence of having
an electron, and therefore

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:33.620
its solution being a
wave function that solves

00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:34.790
the Schrodinger equation.

00:06:34.790 --> 00:06:37.430
It's a consequence
of having that

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:40.730
in the context of a
periodic potential.

00:06:40.730 --> 00:06:43.010
You can't get around it.

00:06:43.010 --> 00:06:43.970
It's a theorem.

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:50.500
So because of
Bloch's theorem, you

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:52.523
got to have this
requirement, if you

00:06:52.523 --> 00:06:54.190
want to think about
it as a requirement,

00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:58.090
that when the wave
function repeats,

00:06:58.090 --> 00:06:59.440
the properties just repeat.

00:06:59.440 --> 00:07:01.180
